Aigning the second div in the centre of the first div.


<div class="out">
  <div class="in"></div>
</div>


.out{
    height: 300px;
    width: 300px;
    background-color: yellow;
    /* position: relative; */
    position: absolute;
}

.in{
    height: 100px;
    width: 100px;
    background-color: green;
    position: relative;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%,-50%);//The translate() method moves an element from its current position (according to the parameters given for the X-axis and the Y-axis).
}
